list.comment: Changes to City. Removed city child classes. Added difficulty for questions to question files. __EASY , __NORMAL, __HARD words in the begining of the line will be used to mark difficulty. Changed Question load()

task.summary:
Added logic to change Questions - package aplication.classes.cities. Added Ranking, Score Player classes, not implemented. TO DO Logic for displaying scores, keeping scores, scores.fxml, ScoresController. Added BootController with boot.fxml for startscreen. TO DO Team Rift Logo displayed for 3-4 seconds, then start screen. Added mordorQuestions. Limited Questions to 8 cities - Blagoevgrad, Burgas, Sofia, Varna, Pleven, Plovdiv, Ruse and Veliko Turnovo. If anyone wants other city, should replace one of above, but first notify others to avoid breaking logic in application.classes.cities; Moved all FXML to resources/fxml. path fixed. Created rankings.txt to keep scores. Added Values.java file to keep all Strings, Dimensions and any other static values. LAYOUT AND DESIGN
TO DO Find good background image.
CHANGES Changed bulgaria map image. Changed start.fxml buttons positon. Changed cities.fxml layout. Layout and design changes. More layout and design changes.

Added new labels at menu, rankings, cities, questions.
Added Utils methods to style Buttons.
Changed hyperlinks to buttons in cities.fxml
Fixed bg flag at menu.fxml
To do :
style
rankings.fxml , quesitons.fxml
functionality user name, user score and max score labels at quizWindow.fxml

Renamed rankings.txt to scores.txt for better flow.
Added new fxml - credits - containing all of the team names.
Added controller for credits.fxml
Scores class:
save() now overrides old user entry if points are higher load() now call create() properly if no scores.txt found. create() creates file and fill with dummy entries. dummy entries replaced on save()
Minor changes to UI.
CreditsController updated. Back button size and text corrected.
Fixed map Fixed map image and buttons offset on lower resolution devices. Test passed at 1280 * 800, 1600 * 900, 3840 * 2160. All font sizes now based on screen dimensions as well.
